From: Ian Campbell <ian.campbell@citrix.com>
Date: Thu, 6 Oct 2011 11:10:48 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 51/56] net: use DMA_x_DEVICE and dma_mapping_error with
 skb_frag_dma_map
Patch-mainline: v3.2-rc1
Git-commit: 5d6bcdfe38ce883946aebf751a64695471ce1ab5 (partial)
References: bsc#911105 FATE#317501

When I converted some drivers from pci_map_page to skb_frag_dma_map I
neglected to convert PCI_DMA_xDEVICE into DMA_x_DEVICE and
pci_dma_mapping_error into dma_mapping_error.

Signed-off-by: Ian Campbell <ian.campbell@citrix.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Gary Ching-Pang Lin <glin@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/cisco/enic/enic_main.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/cisco/enic/enic_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/cisco/enic/enic_main.c
@@ -358,7 +358,7 @@ static inline void enic_queue_wq_skb_con
 		enic_queue_wq_desc_cont(wq, skb,
 			skb_frag_dma_map(&enic->pdev->dev,
 					 frag, 0, frag->size,
-					 PCI_DMA_TODEVICE),
+					 DMA_TO_DEVICE),
 			frag->size,
 			(len_left == 0),	/* EOP? */
 			loopback);
@@ -477,7 +477,7 @@ static inline void enic_queue_wq_skb_tso
 				(unsigned int)WQ_ENET_MAX_DESC_LEN);
 			dma_addr = skb_frag_dma_map(&enic->pdev->dev, frag,
 						    offset, len,
-						    PCI_DMA_TODEVICE);
+						    DMA_TO_DEVICE);
 			enic_queue_wq_desc_cont(wq, skb,
 				dma_addr,
 				len,
